Use the standard library
This is how to rounded_avg of n and m:
  Remember that avg is quotient of sum of n and m and 2
  Remember that bits is "0b"
  Remember that place is 1
  Do this avg times:
    When remainder of quotient of avg and place and 2 is 1, then:
      Remember that bits is "{bits}1"
    But, if not:
      Remember that bits is "{bits}0"
    End when
    Remember that place is product of place and 2
    When place is more than avg, then:
      Leave the loop
    End when
  End do
  The answer is bits
Now you know